The paper discusses the use of computer programs and visualization methods to analyze scientific excellence in different regions of the world. This suggests that it may fall under the categories of data mining (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), spatial information systems (cs.SI), cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY), or graphics (cs.GR). However, given the focus on analyzing scientific publications, the first two categories (cs.DL and cs.IR) are the most likely.
